Second Lady Karen Pence has announced the appointment of Jana Toner as Deputy Assistant to the President and Chief of Staff to the Second Lady. Toner is an experienced leader in personnel, communications, and management and previously served in the Administration of President George W. Bush. Toner joins the Office of the Second Lady from her role as Associate Director in the Office of Presidential Personnel and White House Liaison for the U.S. Department of Education. Kristan King Nevins, the former Chief of Staff, has departed to lead the office of Representative Will Hurd of Texas.